2.20	Beyond_Words_Publishing	Beyond Words Publishing	Beyond Words Publishing is a book publishing company located in Hillsboro, Oregon, United States. Founded in 1983, the company was unprofitable in its early years, though its works were award winning. The privately owned company focuses on non-fiction titles in the New Age genre, but began as a publisher of coffee table books. Beyond Words has a national distribution agreement with Simon &amp; Schusterâ€™s Altria Books imprint and has published works by John Gray, Masaru Emoto, and Rhonda Byrne, including her book The Secret.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/91/Beyond_Words_Publishing_logo.png/200px-Beyond_Words_Publishing_logo.png
